[ELEPHANTS TRUMPETING]

1339
01:38:13,080 --> 01:38:15,230
LAWYER:
Yes, Mrs. Benson. I know. I know.

1340
01:38:15,400 --> 01:38:17,356
But it's wills-ville time in Dixie.

1341
01:38:17,520 --> 01:38:20,592
And we've got to face the facts,
death-wise, that is.

1342
01:38:20,760 --> 01:38:22,398
I'll give it to you short and sweet.

1343
01:38:22,560 --> 01:38:26,633
You get all the moo, all of it,
but there's one catch.

1344
01:38:28,480 --> 01:38:31,358
"And so I order to be built
the Pinky Benson Memorial Museum...

1345
01:38:31,520 --> 01:38:33,033
...dedicated to my fans.

1346
01:38:33,200 --> 01:38:36,636
And within it will be preserved all
my dancing shoes dipped in bronze...

1347
01:38:36,800 --> 01:38:39,234
...and a giant gold replica
of my larynx.

1348
01:38:39,400 --> 01:38:41,994
A permanent pink light
will burn before my statue...

1349
01:38:42,160 --> 01:38:46,870
...and in the 15,000-seat auditorium,
my pictures will run 24 hours a day.

1350
01:38:47,040 --> 01:38:50,953
Everything else I bequeath to my wife,
Louisa May Benson".

1351
01:38:52,720 --> 01:38:54,119
Pinky was right.

1352
01:38:54,280 --> 01:38:56,635
He did belong to his fans.

1353
01:38:56,800 --> 01:38:58,552
Forever.

1354
01:38:58,960 --> 01:39:01,952
He was such a sweet man
when I met him.

1355
01:39:02,120 --> 01:39:03,678
And then came...?

1356
01:39:03,840 --> 01:39:05,478
Well, that's all.

1357
01:39:05,640 --> 01:39:08,074
Why, isn't that enough?

1358
01:39:08,680 --> 01:39:11,114
Oh, I was left with another
$30 million...

1359
01:39:11,280 --> 01:39:14,716
...and I flew right here to Washington,
and that brings us up to date.

1360
01:39:15,400 --> 01:39:16,913
And I wanna give that money away.

1361
01:39:17,080 --> 01:39:19,878
The government's not gonna stop me,
and neither are you.

1362
01:39:20,040 --> 01:39:22,634
Please answer my question,
Dr. Steffanson.

1363
01:39:22,800 --> 01:39:25,553
Am I a witch or am I not?

1364
01:39:29,120 --> 01:39:32,430
Well, you haven't said anything
for the last two husbands.

1365
01:39:37,000 --> 01:39:39,514
- You're not even listening to me.
- Who?

1366
01:39:39,680 --> 01:39:41,875
- What?
- Well, you're an analyst.

1367
01:39:42,040 --> 01:39:45,112
- Well, analyze.
- Oh, that. Yes.

1368
01:39:45,280 --> 01:39:50,195
Now, let me see, you got married
to four men for love.

1369
01:39:50,360 --> 01:39:52,635
All of them were doomed
to success and extinction.

1370
01:39:52,800 --> 01:39:55,598
There was Hopper, Flint, Anderson
and Benson.

1371
01:39:55,760 --> 01:39:59,196
And one man, one man you hated.
That was Leonard Crawley.

1372
01:39:59,360 --> 01:40:01,635
Well, that's a very strong emotion,
hate.

1373
01:40:01,800 --> 01:40:03,791
Say, you know, I think...

1374
01:40:04,160 --> 01:40:06,833
Wait, what do you expect of me,
instant analysis?

1375
01:40:07,000 --> 01:40:10,390
Why, your case might take 24 hours
a day for the next 50 years.

1376
01:40:10,560 --> 01:40:12,915
In other words, Louisa...

1377
01:40:14,320 --> 01:40:16,390
...will you marry me?

1378
01:40:17,200 --> 01:40:19,589
- Dr. Steffanson...
- If it's simplicity you want...

1379
01:40:19,760 --> 01:40:22,752
...you should see my apartment.
I'm a dedicated man of science...

1380
01:40:22,920 --> 01:40:26,708
...and I'm so tired washing out my
own socks. What do you say, Louisa?

1381
01:40:27,080 --> 01:40:28,911
Victor...

1382
01:40:29,080 --> 01:40:31,389
...I'm honored
that you'd risk your life for me.

1383
01:40:31,560 --> 01:40:34,472
- Thank you.
- But it isn't fair.

1384
01:40:34,640 --> 01:40:35,914
I simply don't love you.

1385
01:40:36,840 --> 01:40:37,875
No?

1386
01:40:38,040 --> 01:40:41,589
But would you mail
my check in for me anyway?

1387
01:40:41,760 --> 01:40:43,830
Oh, please don't feel so bad.

1388
01:40:44,000 --> 01:40:46,116
Maybe you helped me after all.

1389
01:40:46,280 --> 01:40:48,555
I said yes to four men,
and I said no to you.

1390
01:40:48,720 --> 01:40:51,837
- Isn't that progress?
- Of a sort, I guess.

1391
01:40:52,160 --> 01:40:55,118
You see, after listening
to my accumulated life story...

1392
01:40:55,280 --> 01:40:57,748
...you naturally assumed
that I'd say yes.

1393
01:40:57,920 --> 01:41:00,036
But you were wrong.

1394
01:41:00,520 --> 01:41:02,033
Wrong?

1395
01:41:02,520 --> 01:41:04,272
I was wrong.

1396
01:41:05,160 --> 01:41:09,950
I have the strangest
tingling sensation in my...

1397
01:41:10,160 --> 01:41:11,149
[SCREAMS]

1398
01:41:11,320 --> 01:41:13,675
Oh, Dr. Steffan...
Victor, are you all right?

1399
01:41:13,840 --> 01:41:15,751
Wake up, doctor! Oh, dear.

1400
01:41:15,920 --> 01:41:18,753
How do I get...? I've got to...

1401
01:41:20,160 --> 01:41:21,434
- Please help me.
- Excuse me.

1402
01:41:21,600 --> 01:41:24,751
Would you please press that button
and let this thing down?

1403
01:41:24,920 --> 01:41:27,195
Dr. Steffanson.

1404
01:41:39,280 --> 01:41:40,838
LENNY:
Ma'am, I...

1405
01:41:41,000 --> 01:41:42,592
Louisa?

1406
01:41:43,480 --> 01:41:45,755
Leonard Crawley.

1407
01:41:46,400 --> 01:41:48,470
What happened to the doctor?

1408
01:41:48,640 --> 01:41:51,029
Uh, he fell off.

1409
01:41:51,200 --> 01:41:53,236
Well, he always does.

1410
01:41:55,480 --> 01:41:56,799
Dr. Steffanson.

1411
01:41:59,200 --> 01:42:01,031
Doctor?

1412
01:42:01,200 --> 01:42:02,838
Doctor.

1413
01:42:05,240 --> 01:42:06,514
- Leonard.
- Mm?

1414
01:42:06,680 --> 01:42:07,999
You're the custodian here.

1415
01:42:08,160 --> 01:42:11,311
Well, now, Louisa, let's call
a spade a spade.

1416
01:42:11,480 --> 01:42:12,959
I'm the janitor here.

1417
01:42:13,120 --> 01:42:16,078
- Oh, how awful.
- Oh, no, no.

1418
01:42:16,240 --> 01:42:18,629
I deserved it. You know,
poetic justice, it's called.

1419
01:42:18,840 --> 01:42:22,276
- But in a way I ruined your life too.
- LENNY: Oh, no, you made it.

1420
01:42:22,800 --> 01:42:26,429
You know, when I lost everything,
I just began to live.

1421
01:42:26,600 --> 01:42:31,435
And I'll always be grateful to you
and your friend.

1422
01:42:31,600 --> 01:42:34,353
- Thoreau.
- He said simplify.

1423
01:42:34,520 --> 01:42:37,990
And you can't get much more simpler
than being a janitor.

1424
01:42:38,800 --> 01:42:40,313
Leonard...

1425
01:42:40,600 --> 01:42:43,239
...you're the only man in the world
I ever really hated.

1426
01:42:44,400 --> 01:42:46,630
Hate's a very strong emotion,
you know.

1427
01:42:46,800 --> 01:42:50,076
But I think the thing
I hated most was that I knew...

1428
01:42:50,240 --> 01:42:52,549
...that deep down
under that small-town emperor...

1429
01:42:52,720 --> 01:42:55,632
...there was a human being
that I wanted to know...

1430
01:42:55,800 --> 01:42:58,075
...and you wouldn't let come out.

1431
01:43:21,080 --> 01:43:23,719
- LOUISA: Leonard, lunch.
- Okay, Mom.

1432
01:43:23,880 --> 01:43:26,155
All right, honey,
now you spread these around.

1433
01:43:26,320 --> 01:43:29,232
Jonathan. Lunch.

1434
01:43:31,040 --> 01:43:33,713
Hey, look, Mom.
Look what I caught.

1435
01:43:33,880 --> 01:43:35,791
- Sharks.
- Well, wonderful.

1436
01:43:35,960 --> 01:43:38,633
We'll have these for dinner.
Now, help your brother.

1437
01:43:38,800 --> 01:43:41,917
Geraldine. Lunch, honey.

1438
01:43:43,960 --> 01:43:49,637
- Now, don't you drop this.
- What do you think I am, a baby?

1439
01:43:49,800 --> 01:43:50,835
[BABY CRYING]

1440
01:43:51,000 --> 01:43:53,912
All right. All right,
help is on the way.

1441
01:43:59,920 --> 01:44:01,273
Okay.

1442
01:44:01,440 --> 01:44:04,273
All right, children.
You can start your milk now.

1443
01:44:04,440 --> 01:44:05,998
Aren't we gonna wait for daddy?

1444
01:44:06,160 --> 01:44:08,913
Nope. Daddy's finishing the plowing
he started this morning.

1445
01:44:13,800 --> 01:44:17,918
And the princess
had four beautiful children.

1446
01:44:18,080 --> 01:44:20,992
ALL:
Leonard and Jonathan...

1447
01:44:21,160 --> 01:44:24,232
...and Geraldine and Butch.

1448
01:44:24,400 --> 01:44:29,235
And they all lived happily ever after.

1449
01:44:29,400 --> 01:44:31,118
[RUMBLING]

1450
01:44:51,520 --> 01:44:53,715
LENNY:
Louisa.

1451
01:44:53,920 --> 01:44:55,638
Louisa.

1452
01:44:55,840 --> 01:44:58,593
It's oil. It's oil!

1453
01:44:59,360 --> 01:45:00,998
Louisa. Look, it's oil!

1454
01:45:01,160 --> 01:45:04,038
It's oil. Look at it!

1455
01:45:05,200 --> 01:45:08,351
It can't be happening.
It can't be true.

1456
01:45:08,520 --> 01:45:10,556
It can't be happening.

1457
01:45:10,720 --> 01:45:14,269
But it is, Louisa. It's real.

1458
01:45:16,320 --> 01:45:19,198
Hey, look at this. It's real.
It's oil.

1459
01:45:19,360 --> 01:45:20,918
You bet it's real. And it's ours.

1460
01:45:21,080 --> 01:45:23,310
- Yours?
- Yes, you idiot. It belongs to us.

1461
01:45:23,480 --> 01:45:25,789
You punched a hole in our pipeline.

1462
01:45:25,960 --> 01:45:29,316
- It's not ours?
- No, it's ours.

1463
01:45:35,440 --> 01:45:39,069
My wonderful, wonderful failure.

1464
01:46:18,200 --> 01:46:20,191
Subtitles by
SDI Media Group

1465
